TopicTitle: [WIP][1.9.x-1.12.x] Scatterer-atmospheric scattering (0.0838 - 14/08/2022) Scattering improvements, in-game atmo generation and multi-sun support

Articles.Content:
3 minutes ago, Ghosty141 said:

Interesting, Eskandare and me have the same processor and we both have the same issue. Maybe it's AMD related ?

I have an i7 2600K and I'm having the same issue

40 minutes ago, kendoka15 said:

I have an i7 2600K and I'm having the same issue

I've got an Intel i7 and an Nvidia graphics card and I'm also having issues.

Is the current version ONLY for 1.1? I am trying to run  v0.024 in 1.0.5 1028 with no luck. The add-on does not begin and there is no menu. Im continuing to troubleshoot but I am sure previous versions -did- work.

17 minutes ago, Raideur Ng said:

Is the current version ONLY for 1.1? I am trying to run  v0.024 in 1.0.5 1028 with no luck. The add-on does not begin and there is no menu. Im continuing to troubleshoot but I am sure previous versions -did- work.

Yes. Short answer: Unity 5 uses different functions than the previous versions, and the 1.1 update is basically made to use those new ones.
Lovely. I do not have a Steam version so apparently I have to wait for the official release..

8 hours ago, selfish_meme said:

Haha, I'm digging the KSC being tsunamied, this wave moves back and forth consuming the KSC, I have the new EVE installed, running on OpenGL of course

I don't think I am getting light scattering

 

Edit: Removed EVE still the same

I'm seeing the same behavior. I'm running a fresh install of 1.1 with no other mods, on Linux.

7 minutes ago, minego said:

I'm seeing the same behavior. I'm running a fresh install of 1.1 with no other mods, on Linux.

@blackrack can't run OpenGL at the moment till Squad fix it for Windows, so we can stop reporting this until he can.
In 1.1 with the latest version there are no shaders whatsoever and nothing happens.

2 hours ago, minego said:

I'm seeing the same behavior. I'm running a fresh install of 1.1 with no other mods, on Linux.

Ditto, on Linux.  Getting 150m black waves of doom.  In a way that's kinda cool....but I might tire of it eventually.

Let me know if any more information would be helpful.

Cheers,

-BS
